      "content": "yeah \"improving user experience\" is what they always say. but the timing is so weird. i was looking at the packet headers and they don't look like standard telemetry. they look like fragments of real-time sys data being pushed to a centralized hub. it feels less like error reporting and more like they're building a massive, real-time map of user thought patterns or something. if you look at the scale of it, could this actually be an intentional mechanism for large-scale data harvesting—like, something much bigger than just \"ads\" or \"diagnostics\"?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
